The paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on generating paraphrases, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper proposes a deep generative framework that combines VAE and LSTM models, which are commonly used in machine learning and deep learning research, respectively. Therefore, the paper is likely to be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (machine learning), cs.AI (artificial intelligence), cs.NE (neural and evolutionary computing), and cs.CV (computer vision), which are all closely related to NLP and deep learning.
